===Etymology===
From Medieval Latin [[machicolatus|machicolātus]], past participle of [[machicolare|machicolāre]], from Old French [[machicoller]], from [[machicolleis]], ''machicolation'', from Old Provençal [[machacol]], from [[macar]], ''to crush'' + [[col]], ''neck''.

===Verb===
'''machicolate'''

# To furnish with [[machicolation]]s.

